Welcome to the Creator Cafe

Welcome!

You can think of it as a café that people work out of. You can come, do your own thing, be around people who are working, and connect with a few when you and they are free.
I have modeled the café according to the Eudaimonia Machine mentioned in the book Deep Work and below are the spaces that are available.
🛋️
Shallow Work
🤫
Deep Work
☕
Lounge
📘
Reading Space
🎨
Gallery
Drop in and out whenever you feel like it, with no obligation to come in at a certain time or stay for a certain time. Even if there is no one else there, you can hang out and continue your work.
 
If you have any feedback, DM me on Twitter @kavirkaycee

FAQs

How do I change status / inform others what I am working on?
How do I chat with others?
Right side panel for chatting with others
Chat
Select Chat (speech bubble icon) in the navigation barto view any messages you've received while in the Space, as well as to send messages to others. While there are some basic features, chat works a little differently based on what type of Space you're in: Tip: You can quickly tell what type of Space you're in by looking at the navigation bar.
https://support.gather.town/help/chat
Can I use Creator Café on mobile?
Yes you can, but best experience on laptop
Gather Mobile
While the Gather mobile experience is still a work in progress, we're excited that you can now use Gather on your smartphone or tablet! The following article provides basic information on how to use Gather on a smart device. Notes: Your experience may vary slightly based on your device's operating system and browser.
https://support.gather.town/help/gather-mobile

How do I get notifications when people join?
Go to Settings, then User, then Space Notifications

What’s the etiquette of joining people on tables
You are free to join others on tables that are outside of the deep work space. If anyone is in deep work, the expectation is that they are not to be disturbed
